<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-532-902  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 532 902.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  June 4 1990 n370 p171(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Dealers face high-end microsystems: sales and support of moresophisticated demands.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Reagan, Joan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Many in the computer reseller channel are hearing from businessthat the days of buying microcomputers piecemeal are over and nowthey want fully integrated systems.andP;  The challenge for resellerswill be in making the transformation from selling computers asboxed commodities to selling full, enterprisewide solutions.andO;Resellers will have to retrain their salespeople to work withcompanies in solving systems problems, rather than just sellinghardware.andP;  The shift in demand may actually be good for resellersbecause of the shrinking margins on microcomputer hardware.andO;Selling complete solutions gives resellers an opportunity to addvalue to their sales through service, support, maintenance andtraining options.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Dealers and AgentsMicrocomputersComputer RetailingCompatible HardwareSystem DesignComputer Systems Integration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>